						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar in the museum with in the compound of the Sōmēśvara temple. First pillar (Museum No. 81).</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">1077 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>It registers a gift of forty goats for a perpetual lamp to the god Sōmēśvaradēva of Koḷḷipāke by <hi rend="italic">mahāmandaḷēśvara</hi> Eṟuve Toṇḍarasa, Dēmarasa and Kāmaṇa.</p>						

						<p>This record has been engraved as a continuation of No. 34 and is dated Śaka 999, Pingala, Jyeshtha, śu. 13, Monday. It corresponds to 1077 A.D., May 8., Jyeshṭha month was adhika.</p>						

						</summary>
